{"id":"0902.1462","submitter":"Amit Rai","authors":"Amit Rai and G. S. Agarwal","title":"Possibility of Coherent Phenomena like Bloch Oscillations with Single\n  Photons via W-States","comments":"5 pages, 7 figures","journal-ref":"PHYSICAL REVIEW A 79, 053849 (2009)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.79.053849","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph cond-mat.other","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We examine the behavior of single photons at multiport devices and inquire if\ncoherent effects are possible. In particular we study how single photons need\nto be manipulated in order to study coherent phenomena. We show that single\nphotons need to be produced in W states which lead to vanishing mean amplitude\nbut nonzero correlations between the inputs at different ports. Such\ncorrelations restore coherent effects with single photons. As a specific\nexample we demonstrate Bloch oscillations with single photons and thus provide\nstrict analog of Bloch oscillation of electrons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Feb 2009 15:39:57 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 30 Nov 2009 20:18:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-13"}
